==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Maidmarian
<hw>Maid`ma"ri*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Maid</ets>
+ <ets>Marian</ets>, relating to <ets>Mary</ets>, or the Virgin
<ets>Mary</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The lady of the May games; one
of the characters in a morris dance; a May queen. Afterward, a grotesque
character personated in sports and buffoonery by a man in woman's
clothes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A kind of dance.</def> <rj><au>Sir W.
Temple.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Maidpale</ent>⟦br⟧
